HEADWORD: Roturier
<hw>Ro`tu`rier"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>A person who is not of noble birth; specif., a freeman who during
the prevalence of feudalism held allodial land.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

